OL,6,FDetective Constable Beth Otty said:
OL,7,F"Ramsey and Hurst should have been
OL,8,Fkeeping the victim safe, instead they
OL,9,Fwere the ones who groomed her,
OL,10,Fsexually assaulted and abused her.
OL,12,F"She should have been able to trust
OL,13,Fthem and should have felt safe in
OL,14,Ftheir company.
OL,16,F"They had no forethought for the
OL,17,Flasting impact their actions will
OL,18,Fcontinue to have on the victim.
